{"key":"post-9445031","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9445031</id>\n<content>Correct.&amp;nbsp; Nobody goes out and buys a can of coffee to grow mushrooms on.&amp;nbsp; It's the waste grinds that we throw away anyway, or if we're non-mushroom growers we should be dumping on our garden or houseplants as soil conditioner and fertilizer.&amp;nbsp; You don't need to pH balance the coffee grinds.&amp;nbsp; Mushroom mycelium prefers an acidic substrate and will colonize it quickly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can use pf cakes to inoculate the coffee and phonebooks.&amp;nbsp; One or two cakes or a quart of grain is what I use per phonebook.&amp;nbsp; Just cut out a section in the middle of the book to dump the spawn.&amp;nbsp; I also drill a bunch of 1/4&quot; holes all over the book, because it makes little tunnels that the mycelium can easily crawl through to speed up colonization.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more ideas, search posts by waxingren in the gourmet forum.&amp;nbsp; He's got some cool newspaper grows and one or two on used breakfast cereal boxes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9448619</next>\n<prev>9444556</prev>\n<first>9439558</first>\n<last>19239340</last>\n<when>1229472229</when>\n<utime>12/17/08 02:03 AM</utime>\n</post>"}